> personally seen explode at a tire shop while getting new tire mounted.  >>
>
> Any feedback on "Slime" pre-puncture sealant...A buddy of mine uses it
> on his strictly farm-used pickup and swears by it. Just curious about
> street use...

I use it in my motorcycles in tubed tires.  Works great if the puncture is
in the tread area, but not for punctures in the sidewall region.  It would
make a mess if you used it in a tubeless tire.  Let the tire guy know
before he dismounts a "slimed" tubeless tire!


